refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;

 stringfalsesession_module_name
 stringnullmodule&null;



 session_module_name gets the name of the current
 session module, which is also known as
 session.save_handler.

&reftitle.parameters;
module
If module is specified and not &null;, that module will be used instead. Passing "user" to this parameter is forbidden. Instead session_set_save_handler has to be called to set a user defined session handler.

&reftitle.changelog;





    &Version;
    &Description;





    8.0.0

     module is nullable now.




    7.2.0

     It is now explicitly forbidden to set the module name to
     "user". Formerly, this has been silently ignored.
